          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the best GBP management tool for a single-location business?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">For a single location, theStacc Local SEO ($49/mo) handles GBP content creation. Add BrightLocal ($39/mo) for rank tracking and auditing. Start with Google Business Profile (free) if you haven't completed your profile yet. Total cost: $88/month for content + tracking.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How often should I post to my Google Business Profile?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">3–5 times per week is the sweet spot. Businesses posting daily or near-daily consistently rank higher in local pack results. At minimum, post once per week. theStacc creates 30 posts per month — roughly one per day — which keeps your profile active without any manual effort.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Do GBP posts actually help with local rankings?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. Google has confirmed that profile activity is a local ranking factor. GBP posts signal that your business is active and engaged, and they provide keyword-rich content Google indexes. Businesses that post regularly see measurable improvements in local pack visibility within 4–8 weeks.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can I manage my GBP without any paid tools?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. Google Business Profile is free and includes posting, review response, photo uploads, and basic analytics. The limitation is time — everything is manual. If you can dedicate 3–5 hours per week to GBP management, you don't need paid tools. Most business owners can't, which is why these tools exist.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How do I track my Google Maps ranking?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">BrightLocal and Local Falcon both offer geo-grid rank tracking. They scan your Google Maps position across a geographic grid and produce a visual heatmap showing where you rank by neighborhood — not just a single position number. Costs range $24.99–59/month depending on the tool and frequency.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Is it worth paying for GBP post creation?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">A well-written GBP post takes 10–15 minutes. At 30 posts per month, that's 5–7.5 hours of work. If your time is worth more than $6.50/hour, theStacc at $49/month is more cost-effective than writing posts yourself — and the quality is more consistent when content is created systematically.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What happens if I stop using a GBP management tool?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
